body: Chill guys. This is just JAV actress's story. You used to watch a lot of porn videos during your puberty. So calm down and don't call her hoe.

拿自己的学业和清白，换句话说，立足之本，去赌一个屌子对自己的真心，这女人真是天生的婊子。
这种婊子明明只配一辈子卖肉过活，最后居然还被刻画得这么幸福，我觉得作者非蠢即坏，或者活在天上。

Too ignorant to deserve freedom, this bitch could never make a difference in real life.
To work hard is to shine and get happy? Capitalists love to exploit you by this rhetoric.

And before anyone screeches at me for ruining their "wholesome" little story, don't bother. I won't see it and I don't think I said anything controversial. The story would've been way more wholesome if she distanced herself from porn and turned towards a genuinely fulfilling career, showing her ex, herself and everyone around her how brightly she can shine with her own light. Prostitution/AV doesn't open doors. It closes them.

What a sad coping mechanism, telling yourself that you're happy where you are just because a bunch of strangers online seem to care about you through a screen. She sucks dick for a living and thinks people are supporting her out of love and admiration. She's nothing more than fap material. She's not changing the world, acquiring a skill or doing something fulfilling. She gets sweet dopamine from sex and feels fulfilled from positive feedback. That's empty and depressing. This momentary sense of belonging will be completely shattered once she's not attractive anymore, or her company goes under and she has to sign shady contracts to survive, or she gets an STD and has to completely quit her "career," the list goes on. Maybe my opinion is negatively affected by western porn, but I can't seem to see this as anything other than postponing the inevitable. And honestly, at that point I can only say she deserved it.
